# Been There, Done That: Journal App

This is a simple app that lets you create basic posts and journal about what you did, a feeling you had, or something odd you experienced that day. You can input a filename after and the posts will be saved for later access.

## Instructions for Build and Use

Steps to build and/or run the software:

1. You will need npm installed and up to date.
2. Download the Expo app from the app store on your Android or Apple device.
3. Run npx expo start --tunnel in the terminal. The app will bundle and a QR code will appear in the terminal
4. Scan that code on your device in the Expo app. The app will then load on your phone.

Instructions for using the software:

1. Once the app has loaded, you can click through the various screens. Trying to enter any username won't work yet, so just create a post.
2. Enter whatever text you'd like, then Save the post by clicking the button at the bottom of the Posts screen. Enter a username there.
3. Upon returning to the app later, you can put that username in and your posts will be loaded anew. (This is local storage only for now)

## Development Environment

To recreate the development environment, you need the following software and/or libraries with the specified versions:

* expo (I had to use SDK 54.0.0)
* react-navigation/native and react-navigation-system
* expo-file-system (mine resulted in a high security vulnerability, which I resolved with npm audit fix)

